.SH "NAME"
oo \- syntactic sugar for Moo oneliners
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  perl \-Moo=Foo \-e \*(Aqhas bar => ( is => q[ro], default => q[baz] ); print Foo\->new\->bar\*(Aq
\&
\&  # loads an existing class and re\-"opens" the package definition
\&  perl \-Moo=+My::Class \-e \*(Aqprint _\|_PACKAGE_\|_\->new\->bar\*(Aq
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
oo.pm is a simple source filter that adds \f(CW\*(C`package $name; use Moo;\*(C'\fR to the
beginning of your script, intended for use on the command line via the \-M
option.
